<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title inertia><%= content_for(:title) || "Starter Base Inertia" %></title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-capable" content="yes">
    <meta name="mobile-web-app-capable" content="yes">
    <%= csp_meta_tag %>

    <%#
      DARK MODE FLASH PREVENTION (FOUC)

      This inline <style> + <script> block prevents the flash of unstyled content (FOUC)
      when switching between light/dark themes. This is the industry-standard approach
      used by Next.js (next-themes), Remix, and other modern frameworks.

      WHY IT MUST BE HERE:
      - Script runs BEFORE page renders (blocking)
      - Inline styles load BEFORE external CSS
      - Can't use external files (too slow)
      - Can't use CSS variables (not defined yet)
      - MUST hardcode color values to match --sidebar variable

      HOW IT WORKS:
      1. Inline <style> sets background colors based on .dark class
      2. Script reads theme from localStorage
      3. Script adds .dark class to <html> if needed
      4. Browser paints with correct colors immediately
      5. React/CSS loads and takes over

      Reference: https://github.com/pacocoursey/next-themes
    %>
    <style>
      /* Prevent white flash - colors match --background variable from application.css (corporate theme) */
      html, body {
        background-color: oklch(0.98 0 0); /* Light mode: --background */
      }
      html.dark, html.dark body {
        background-color: oklch(0.26 0.03 262.67); /* Dark mode: --background */
      }
    </style>

    <script>
      // Apply theme class immediately (blocking script)
      try {
        const theme = localStorage.getItem('ui-theme') || 'system';
        const isDark = theme === 'dark' || (theme === 'system' && window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches);

        if (isDark) {
          document.documentElement.classList.add('dark');
        }
      } catch (e) {}
    </script>

    <%= yield :head %>

    <%# Enable PWA manifest for installable apps (make sure to enable in config/routes.rb too!) %>
    <%#= tag.link rel: "manifest", href: pwa_manifest_path(format: :json) %>

    <link rel="icon" href="/icon.png" type="image/png">
    <link rel="icon" href="/icon.svg" type="image/svg+xml">
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/icon.png">

    <%= vite_react_refresh_tag %>
    <%= vite_client_tag %>
    <%= vite_javascript_tag "inertia.tsx" %>
    <%= inertia_ssr_head %>
    <!--
      If using a TypeScript entrypoint file:
        vite_typescript_tag 'application'

      If using a .jsx or .tsx entrypoint, add the extension:
        vite_javascript_tag 'application.jsx'

      Visit the guide for more information: https://vite-ruby.netlify.app/guide/rails
    -->

  </head>

  <body>
    <%= yield %>
  </body>
</html>
